body:
I've recently upgraded from Groovy 3.x to 4.x. As part of that upgrade, my `:checkLicense` task (using https://github.com/jk1/Gradle-License-Report) has identified that `groovy-bom` has no license:

```json
{
    "dependenciesWithoutAllowedLicenses": [
        {
            "moduleLicense": null,
            "moduleVersion": "4.0.1",
            "moduleName": "org.apache.groovy:groovy-bom"
        }
    ]
}
```

I'm assuming that groovy-bom is under Apache (as the rest of Groovy). I don't know if this is the "correct" way to add a license for `:checkLicense`. 

I'm guessing https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/master/gradle/licenses.gradle needs to be updated too?

This does not cover `map['foo'] = 'bar'` which routes through "getAt" (by design, I think).

This also covers:
```groovy
class C extends HashMap<String,Object> {
  @groovy.transform.CompileStatic
  void m() {
    foo = 'bar'
  }
}
```

https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6954
